Linux Commands 7/8/2026

grep - find words or patterns in files, may include regex or case-insensitive

wc - lists the lines in a file, including txt and .dat files

netstat - check network status and interfaces using -interfaces

cal - for checking the calendar

man - used for instruction or guidance on commands

tar - a compression tool where you state the the flags such as -cvf and the .tar file to be created

-zip a similar tool and often found on Windows from 8-11

-less a file-reading tool for particularly lengthy txt files

-ssh a remote-access protocol for when you need to attain control via CLI of another computer

-scp Secure Copy Protocol for copying files to other systems given their IP, much like SSH

